text: <@U0PB67X4K>: How to logout? You can run “peer network login” to login or POST to registrar through REST API, but there is no logout command
<@U1MJ9SRF0>:   use a DELETE with the `/registrar/{enrollmentID}` endpoint

<@U0PB67X4K>: Thanks for your help. However, if I DELETE the account, I cannot login again to in the same peer
<tent-Type: application/json" -X POST -d '{"enrollId":"diego","enrollSecret":"DRJ23pEQl16a"}' localhost:7050/reg>
{"OK":"Login successful for user 'diego'."}
<ETE localhost:7050/registrar/diego
{"OK":"Deleted login token and directory for user diego."}
<nrollId":"diego","enrollSecret":"DRJ23pEQl16a"}' localhost:7050/registrar
{"Error":"rpc error: code = 2 desc = \"Identity or token does not match.\""}
<@U14RU670C> - yep.  sorry - that is what I was trying to say earlier.  I just commented here:   <https://jira.hyperledger.org/browse/FAB-2>
hopefully that will help explain what is happening - but the bottom line is that "logging out"  with the REST API is not really like logging out in the classic sense.
Using the NodeSDK is the way to go moving forward
<@U0PB67X4K>: That explains it well. But is there any method to create a new one-time password for a user?
That’s quite said to hear that. Anyway, thanks for your help. It clears my questions about the login feature available at the moment.:slightly_smiling_face:
I will take part onto the following Meetup mit Blockchain Meetup Saxony teil <http://meetu.ps/e/BSX3Y/tyVjx/d>
